#limitation(title: [Multi-Omics Reproducibility])[
Most multi-omics studies in ME/CFS are single-cohort analyses with small sample sizes (n$<$50). Validation in independent cohorts is essential before molecular subtypes can be considered clinically actionable. Standardization of sample collection, processing, and analytical pipelines across sites remains a major challenge. The ME/CFS Biobank initiatives (UK, US, European) are addressing these issues through harmonized protocols.
]
